<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German President Meets Chinese Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- German President Roman Herzog met
with visiting Chinese leader Li Ruihuan here today, and stressed
that Li's visit marked the return of German-Chinese relations to
the track of healthy development.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, conveyed the cordial regards
from Chinese President Jiang Zemin to the German president, and
said that although this was a short visit, he had achieved a lot
from it.
</P>
<P>
Li said both China and Germany are working for regional and
world peace and stability and for promoting economic
development. Both countries stand for a multi-polarized world and
oppose the situation in which world affairs are decided by one or
two superpowers, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that China and Germany have many points in common
in various fields, such as disarmament and environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
On China's domestic situation, Li said people should understand
China's current position from three aspects. The first is that
China must adhere to Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics. This theory has an extensive and
profound social foundation in the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
The second is that China must maintain unity and social
stability and guard against disturbance, he said. The Chinese
people had the common understanding that only with unity and
stability could the country develop and become strong.
</P>
<P>
The third aspect is that China should work hard to solve,
without delay, thorny problems in the economic and social life, Li
said. China's economic restructuring was going smoothly on the
whole, but there also existed certain problems.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the Chinese people are fully confident they can
handle properly the issues in the three aspects and bring China,
which is full of vigor and vitality, into the coming 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Herzog said that the important visit paid by Li signaled that
relations between Germany and China are back on the track of
healthy development.
</P>
<P>
He said Germany and China are friendly countries and China's
stability and development is of political and economic importance
for Germany.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Germany and the whole world hope to see a
stable and developing China, and Germany is willing to strengthen
its friendly relations and cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Herzog asked Li to extend his cordial regards to Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Li also briefed Herzog on China's Hong Kong
policy. Herzog said Germany is following with great interest Hong
Kong's return to its motherland on July 1. He said this is an
event of great importance, for it represents a new beginning of
the reunification process of China.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also exchanged views on international issues of
common concern. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
