<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Parliament Leader Meets Chinese Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Rita Suessmuth, president of the
Bundestag, the lower house of the German parliament, met here
today with visiting Chinese leader Li Ruihuan.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Li, chairman of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, said
China has always attached importance to Germany's major role in
European and other international affairs, and to China's relations
with Germany.
</P>
<P>
He praised the German parliament for its important influence on
developing Sino-German relations. "We welcome more German
parliamentarians to visit China," Li told Suessmuth.
</P>
<P>
Li also said Suessmuth would be welcomed to visit China, and
briefed her on China's situation.
</P>
<P>
He said it is very important to maintain good relations between
China and Germany. China respects Germany's social system and
values, and has an earnest regard for Germany's opinions and
suggestions about China. China also hoped Germany would respect
China's various choices and views, which were based on its own
national conditions.
</P>
<P>
Suessmuth and Li also, frankly and sincerely, exchanged views
on democracy and human rights.
</P>
<P>
Suessmuth said Li's visit will surely help enhance mutual
understanding between the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
