<HEADLINE> FIFA Clears Spanish Referee of 'Corruption' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, June 11 (Xinhua) -- World football body FIFA on
Wednesday said it had found there was no evidence to suggest
that Spanish referee Manuel Diaz Vega had favoured Swiss team in
 a World Cup qualifier last November.
</P>
<P>
Vega took charge of the match between Switzerland and Norway on
November 10 in Berne, following which there were allegations in
the Swiss media that Kurt Roethlisberger had acted as an
intermediary to try to persuade the Spanish official to favour the
Swiss team.
</P>
<P>
Roethlisberger was suspended for life by UEFA and FIFA in April
after they found him guilty of attempted corruption in a
Champions League match between Grasshopper Zurich and AJ Auxerre
last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
