<HEADLINE> PKK Kills 5 Military Personnel in Southeastern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Five Turkish military personnel
were killed in armed clashes between the Turkish security forces
and the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in southeastern
province of Bingol within 24 hours, an official statement said
today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the Turkish government troops also wiped out 15
PKK members in the clashes in the rural area of Adakli town in
Bingol.
</P>
<P>
It said that the security forces had captured five PKK
guerrillas in southeastern Turkey and eight PKK members
surrendered to the security forces in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish armed forces are staging military operations both
in southeastern Turkey and northern Iraq to attack the PKK
rebels in this region.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000-strong Turkish government troops, backed by air
power, poured into northern Iraq on May 14 in the cross-border
military operations against the PKK bases which are used for
raids into southeastern Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
