<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Thrive after Handover: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will continue to
thrive after its return to the motherland, a high-ranking Hong
Kong official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a luncheon meeting of the German Business
Association of Hong Kong, Director-General of Trade Alan Lai said,
"As Hong Kong will become the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR) of the People's Republic of China, "Hong Kong" will
be formally known as "Hong Kong, China" in our participation in
international organizations and conduct of international
relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that HK's beliefs and deeds have withstood the test of
time and changes and such beliefs and deeds will not be changed,
and it is this continuity in a time of change which will make Hong
Kong live and thrive after its return to the motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that Hong Kong will continue to face all these
changes with something that has remained unchanged in all these
years."
</P>
<P>
"It is the same Hong Kong people with the same resilience and
self-reliance," Lai said.
</P>
<P>
"And government and the people share a clear vision of the
economic role of the city: to live and thrive, holding on whatever
we could amidst all changes.
</P>
<P>
"The proven elements of Hong Kong's success have been enshrined
in the Sino-British Joint Declaration and the Basic Law," he
noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
