<HEADLINE> Spirlea into Last Eight in Classic Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONGDON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Irina Spirlea moved
into the last eight of the DFS Classic women's tournament with a
6-3 6-4 win over American Nicole Arendt on in Birmingham,
Britain, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Romanian took just 70 minutes to defeat her
unseeded opponent.
</P>
<P>
Spirlea's next opponent will be Dominique Van Roost, the No 6
seed from Belgium, who had little trouble beating Ginger
Helgeson-Nielsen of America 6-2 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Number three seed Lisa Raymond, also from America, beat
14th-seeded Dutch player Miriam Oremans 6-3 7-6 (7-5) to enter the
last eight.
</P>
<P>
Anne-Gaelle Sidot of France, the number five seed, was not so
lucky. She came up against experienced grass court player Kristine
Kunce, an Australian qualifier, who served and volleyed her way
to win by 6-4 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
