<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Eight people, including three
children, were crushed to death and another seriously injured when
the boundary wall of a petroleum storage and distribution depot in
India's Madhya Pradesh caved in on Wednesday, Press Trust of India
reported today.
</P>
