<HEADLINE> Biggest Forestry Enterprise in Beijing Starts Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A furniture company which is the
largest of its kind founded in Beijing by the Ministry of Forestry
started operations today.
</P>
<P>
This marks a big step forward for China's forestry departments
in making the most of their advantages, said a ministry spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"In recent years, the restructuring of the forestry industry,
done to intensity the processing of timber resources, has always
been a key task for departments at all levels," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The furniture company was jointly financed by the China
State-Owned Forestry Farm Exploring Corporation and a Hong Kong
company. Administered by the Ministry of Forestry, the China
State-Owned Forestry Farm Exploring Corporation invested more than
40 million yuan (nearly 5 million US dollars) to the joint venture.
</P>
<P>
Around 100,000 pieces of furniture will be produced yearly by
the company. Its main products, named "Linpai" (forest), will be
shown at the China Furniture Fair later this year. 
</P>
