<HEADLINE> Party Building in Colleges Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China's colleges should regard the
work of training the successors of the country's socialist
construction as fundamental for building up the Communist Party,
said an official with the State Education Commission (SEC).
</P>
<P>
He urged colleges to balance academics with the cultivation of
ethics, with priority given to ideological and political
construction, said Zhu Kaixuan, minister in charge of the SEC.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting on the Party building of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), which was held yesterday by the Organization
Department and the Propaganda Department of the CPC Central
Committee and the SEC, Zhu stressed that all universities and
colleges should teach students to be both politically conscious
and professionally competent.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Party organizations and Party members serving
in the higher education field should strive to find answers to the
two major issues facing education.
</P>
<P>
One is the need to coordinate with the overall demand of the
modernization drive. The other is that the overall quality and
results of the educational system must be improved, and the
socialist cultural and ethical progress should be further
accelerated.
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out that the first task for the Party organizations
in the near future is to improve the general morale on college
campuses.
</P>
<P>
The Party must also improve its leadership in colleges, and
step up the reform in education on Marxist theories and on
ideology and ethics, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
