<HEADLINE> Two State-Owned Enterprises Auctioned off in Haikou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Haikou Third Rubber Plant and
Haikou Towel Plant have been sold on the auction block at a recent
sale for bankrupt state-owned enterprises, held in the capital of
Hainan, China's southernmost island province.
</P>
<P>
A total of six enterprises joined the bidding. Starting prices
for the rubber and towel plants stood at 16 million and six
million yuan, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Haikou Fu'an Building Materials Company, a subsidiary of
the Yunnan Guohong Real Estate Development Corporation, got the
rubber plant for 13.35 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
And the towel plant was bought by the Hainan Changmao
Enterprise (Group) Company Ltd., headquartered in Guangzhou, which
paid four million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The rubber plant will continue to produce rubber with the
original equipment, technology, and staff, and the towel plant
will be transformed into a medical plant.
</P>
<P>
Several months ago, the two plants declared bankruptcy as a
result of poor management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
