<HEADLINE> First Publication of Mongolian Seal Cutting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China's first calligraphic book
about seal cutting, written in the Mongolian language, has been
printed by a local education publishing house in this capital city
of north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The book's author, Cholemang, teaches at Inner Mongolia
University. In recent years he has conducted extensive studies
into the craft of seal cutting, done both in Chinese and Mongolian
languages.
</P>
<P>
A collection of 800 seal cutting works by ancient artists, and
a number of Cholemang's works are contained in the book.
</P>
<P>
A history of Mongolian seal cutting from the 13th century to
the present is included, along with chapters on cutting
instruments, seal materials, cutting skill and design, and
calligraphic copying.
</P>
<P>
