<HEADLINE> Courier Advances to Last 16 in Queens Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one Jim Courier
of the United States beat South African David Nainkin 6-3, 6-2 to
reach the third round of the Stella Artois Tournament at Queen's
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Seventh seed Courier needed just 30 minutes to win the victory
and set up a third round clash with French Open semi-finalist
Patrick Rafter of Australia later in the day.
</P>
<P>
The remaining second round match was also halted on Thursday
night by rain with Jonas Bjorkman agonisingly close to victory
over Luis Herrera at 7-5, 6-5 ahead.
</P>
<P>
The Swede took it all in his stride however and returned to
court nine for a few minutes this morning to serve out and
complete a 7-5 7-5 win to set up a third round tie with Stephane
Simian of France.
</P>
<P>
Australia's Mark Philippousis became the first player to reach
the quarter-finals after a comfortable 6-3, 6-3 victory over
Zimbabwe's Byron Black. 
</P>
