<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rigid Law Enforcement on Stock Market Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading newspaper, will publish a commentary tomorrow, calling for
more rigid law enforcement on the stock market.
</P>
<P>
The commentary says that the government has repeatedly issued
decrees and documents to ban misconduct in the stock market,
including the flow of bank money into the market, which is in
violation of government rules, and the manipulation of the market
by some listed companies.
</P>
<P>
However, a few institutions and persons have engaged in such
activities recently by ignoring the law and official decrees,
using millions of yuan of capital to cause upheaval in the stock
market.
</P>
<P>
Their actions have harmed the interests of the investors, and
disturbed the normal market order, the commentary points out.
</P>
<P>
In response to the situation, departments concerned have
severely punished responsible persons of banks and companies
involved in the cases in accordance with the law. The move is
meant to ensure the implementation of the regulations of the stock
market, and demonstrates the government's firm resolution to
safeguard the normal order on the market and protect investors'
legitimate rights and interests, the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
It continues to say that to protect the principles for an open,
fair and just stock market and to maintain its healthy
development, the supervision and management systems must be
reinforced, and law enforcement over them must be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
It says that the best way to get to the root of the misconduct
is to cut the illegal flow of bank capital into the stock market,
ban the speculation of stocks by some state-owned enterprises and
listed companies, prevent institutions and big investors from
manipulating the stock market, and standardize the flow of
information and capital.
</P>
<P>
All those who are involved in the stock market must draw
lessons from those charged with misconduct, and avoid committing
the similar mistakes. China will use both the criminal law and
administrative measures to deal with violators, the commentary
says.
</P>
<P>
The standardization and stability of the stock market have a
great bearing on the healthy development of the economy as well as
on social stability. Governments in different regions must attach
great importance to the issue, and take effective measures to
prevent any risks of the stock market from occurrence and remove
them in time, it says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0037 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Prime Minister to Visit Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif will visit Iran on his way back from Turkey to congratulate
Iranian President-elect Muhammad Khatemi.
</P>
<P>
The Afghan issue would also be discussed at the talks between
the Pakistan prime minister and Iranian leaders, Foreign Minister
Gohar Ayub Khan said here today.
</P>
<P>
Sharif will visit Istanbul on June 15-16 to attend the summit
of eight developing countries, named as D-8.  
</P>
</TEXT>
