<HEADLINE> Chinese Company Signs Contract Agreement With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- China Wanbao Engineering
Corporation today signed here with the Ethiopian Electric Light
and Power Authority a contract agreement on the Tis Abay
hydropower project.
</P>
<P>
Acting general manager of the Ethiopian authority Tesfalem
Giyesus and representative of the Chinese company Zhang Shaoyong
signed the agreement on behalf of their respective sides.
</P>
<P>
The over 18.8 million U.S. dollars agreement indicates that
China's electric power equipment will be exported to Ethiopia for
the first time. Under the agreement, the Chinese company will
carry out the supplying, erection and commissioning of two
generators with a capacity of 36 mega watts each and the project
will take 24 months.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese company won the bid after defeating seven foreign
companies from western countries.
</P>
<P>
The Tis Abay hydropower project is located in north-western
part of Ethiopia, more than 560 kms north-west of Addis Ababa.
The project will promote the development of industry and
agriculture in the north-western part of Ethiopia when it is
commissioned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
