<HEADLINE> Largest Sino-US Joint Venture Launched in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai GM Co. and its
subsidiary Pan-Asia Automotive Technical Center, the largest
Sino-US joint project ever, was established today in this economic
and financial center.
</P>
<P>
Jointly funded by Shanghai Automotive Industrial Corporation
and US-based General Motors Corporation (GM) with 1.57 billion US
dollars, the two parties share the equities of the joint venture,
located in Shanghai Pudong Jinqiao Export Processing Zone.
</P>
<P>
Slated to begin manufacturing in 1998, the main model to be
produced by the new joint venture is the "Regal," a mid-luxury
sedan which made its debut in the United States earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The designed production capacity is 100,000 units.
</P>
<P>
Huang Ju, member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC), also secretary of
CPC Shanghai Committee; Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi; James Sasser,
US ambassador to China, and Louis Hughes, GM's executive
president, attended the opening ceremony. 
