<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 13:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poll: Palestinian Jerusalemites Opposed to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A Palestinian opinion poll
shows that the overwhelming majority of the Palestinian
residents in Jerusalem are opposed to Israel's claim of sole
sovereignty over the city.
</P>
<P>
According to the poll, conducted by two researchers, Nader
Sa'id and Jerome Segal, to over 900 Palestinian Jerusalemites,
Jerusalem is of enormous importance to Palestinians, the JMCC, a
Palestinian press service based in East Jerusalem reported today.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-two percent of the interviewees said that it is "very
important" to them personally and 94 percent said no to a
suggestion that Palestinians support Israel's sole sovereignty
over Jerusalem, "even if that would be the only way a Palestinian
state could come into being."
</P>
<P>
Seventy-two percent agree: "In case of an unacceptable
agreement on Jerusalem, Palestinians have the right to use all
means necessary to block its implementation. Thus, it is
extremely unlikely that real peace can be achieved if there is
not a compromise acceptable to both sides on Jerusalem."
</P>
<P>
Most Palestinian Jerusalemites support real peace under
certain conditions. Seventy percent "support genuine and lasting
peace with Israel in exchange for recognition of a Palestinian
state with its capital in East Jerusalem, and resolution of the
refugee issue, even though this will inevitably fall short of
justice for the Palestinians."
</P>
<P>
Palestinian Jerusalemites are open to a variety of proposals
with respect to the future status of the city. These include:
</P>
<P>
-- West Jerusalem under Israeli sovereignty and East Jerusalem
under Palestinian sovereignty, with special arrangement for
Israeli control of the Jewish neighborhoods in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
-- The Palestinians would get sovereignty over the Haram
al-Sharif (ak-Aqsa Mosque) in exchange for Palestinian
recognition of Israeli sovereignty over the Western Wall.
</P>
<P>
-- In the Old City, Israel retains sovereignty over the
Jewish neighborhoods while the Palestinians maintain sovereignty
over the Palestinian neighborhoods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0051 </DOCNO>
