<HEADLINE> Manila to Host 3 ASEAN Meetings Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos said here
today that the Philippines will host three meetings of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) next month.
</P>
<P>
Addressing foreign diplomatic crops during the celebration of
the 99th Independence Day, Ramos said the three yearly meetings
are the ASEAN Ministerial Meeting, the ASEAN Standing Committee
Meeting and the ASEAN Regional Forum.
</P>
<P>
The three meetings coincide with the formal admission of
Myanmar, Cambodia and Laos in July into ASEAN which turns 30 years
old this August, Ramos said.
</P>
<P>
The expanded ASEAN would continue promoting regional
cooperation in concert with "all our friends and dialogue partners
with interests in the Asia-Pacific region," he said.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, and Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
