<HEADLINE> Millions of Dollars in Sponsorship for Media Covering HK Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong business community
is offering 8.7 million HK dollars (1.1 million US dollars) to
sponsor telecommunications, publications and souvenir items for
media representatives who will be covering the handover.
</P>
<P>
A Hong Kong government spokesman said today that 10 commercial
organizations were providing sponsorship.
</P>
<P>
But he noted, "Care has been taken to achieve a careful balance
between maintaining the dignity of the occasion and ensuring that
any acknowledgment for commercial sponsorship is presented in a
subtle manner and with good taste."
</P>
<P>
Users of the Press and Broadcast Center (PBC) on the seventh
floor of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center will be
able to enjoy Hong Kong Telecom's contributions of about 5 million
HK dollars (641,000 US dollars) in the form of a special Internet
service and a business center providing computers and fax
machines, while government operational staff will have the use of
some 750 mobile phones and 60 pagers for communications.
</P>
<P>
A press kit has been prepared by the Government Information
Services for distribution to the media. Production of the carrying
bag to hold the press kit has been arranged by DHL International
at a cost of 300,000 HK dollars (38,462 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Members of the media will receive the bag when they collect the
accreditation card from the Handover Ceremony Coordination Office.
</P>
<P>
Among other useful items, the bag contains a Media Guide Book
which provides information on PBC facilities, useful statistics
and telephone numbers. The Guide Book was sponsored by Hang Seng
Bank.
</P>
<P>
"Our gratitude also extends to the Hong Kong Tourist
Association which has prepared a folder with information for
visitors, a CD-ROM with 250 images of Hong Kong and a map of Wan
Chai with a Dining and Wining Guide," he said.
</P>
<P>
Other sponsored items in the bag include a belt pouch with five
rolls of films from Kodak, a polo-shirt and a baseball cap.
</P>
<P>
Other publications included in the bag are a folder with
background features on Hong Kong, and copies of the Basic Law, the
Sino-British Joint Declaration and the 1997 Hong Kong Annual
Report.
</P>
<P>
A watch with two designs, one by the Government Information
Services and another by a local designer, will also be presented
by the Hong Kong government as a souvenir to the media.  
</P>
