<HEADLINE> Foreign Visitors to S. Africa Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Foreign travellors to South
Africa reached nearly 400,000 for the first qauarter this year,
21 percent higher than the same period of last year, The Central
statistical Service (CSS) announced today.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, CSS head F M Orkin said of all the visitors,
more than 391,000 people came from mainland Africa and other
continent.
</P>
<P>
The top seven countries from which most foreign travellers
came were the United Kingdom, Germany, the United States, France,
Australia, Netherlands and Zimbabwe, Orkin said.
</P>
<P>
There was an increase on the number of travellers from almost
all the countries listed with the exception of Spain, Japan and
Malaysia, he said.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Orkin said, a total of 224,491 South Africans went
abroad in the first quarter of this year, an increase of 22
percent as compared with the same period of last year. 
</P>
