<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Keys Posts of HKSAR Judiciary Filled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Judicial Officers
Recommendation Commission (JORC)(Designate) has unanimously
recommended Justice Litton, Justice Ching and Justice Bokhary be
appointed permanent judges of the Court of Final Appeal (CFA) and
Justice Patrick Chan be appointed chief judge of the High Court on
July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Announcing these recommendations today, Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa said that, in exercise of the duty imposed upon him under
Article 88 of the Basic Law, he would accept them.
</P>
<P>
"The three judges recommended for appointment as permanent
judges of the CFA are all distinguished Justices of Appeal and
were outstanding legal practitioners before they joined the bench.
I am pleased to accept the JORC (Designate)'s recommendation on
their appointments," he said.
</P>
<P>
The JORC (Designate), an independent body set up under Article
88 of the Basic Law for the purpose of advising the Chief
Executive on judicial appointments, recommended on May 20 that
Andrew K.N. Li be appointed chief justice of the HKSAR CFA.
</P>
<P>
"Now that the composition of the CFA is decided, the chief
justice (designate) can finalize preparations for the
establishment of the CFA," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the confidence that "the CFA will play a pivotal role
in the development of Hong Kong's jurisprudence and legal system
in the years to come."
</P>
<P>
On the recommendation of the appointment of the chief judge of
the High Court, Tung said, "I am equally pleased with the JORC
(Designate)'s unanimous recommendation of Justice Patrick Chan as
chief judge of the High Court."
</P>
<P>
"The chief judge of the High Court will be a new post for the
HKSAR judiciary. As president of the Court of Appeal and court
leader of the High Court which will be retitled Court of First
Instance on July 1, Justice Patrick Chan will play a key role in
the HKSAR judiciary after its establishment," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
He stated: "Justice Patrick Chan is highly respected by members
of the Judiciary and the profession for his personal and judicial
qualities."
</P>
<P>
"I am particularly delighted to note that Justice Patrick Chan
was among the first batches of local law graduates from Hong Kong
University's law school. With the establishment of the HKSAR
under the policy of Hong Kong people ruling Hong Kong, there is a
great symbolic significance in having one of Hong Kong's own law
graduates filling a leading position in Hong Kong's judiciary,"
Tung noted.
</P>
<P>
"With all five key posts filled by the most capable and
suitable candidates, the HKSAR Judiciary and indeed Hong Kong's
legal system are not only assured of a smooth transition, it is
poised to continue the development of the common law in Hong Kong
in the new and challenging era ahead," Tung stressed.
</P>
<P>
Article 90 of the Basic Law requires the Chief Executive to
obtain the endorsement of the Legislature on the appointment of
the judges of the CFA and the chief judge of the High Court.
</P>
<P>
On June 14, HKSAR Secretary of Justice Elsie Leung will move a
motion to seek support from the Provisional Legislative Council
(PLC) for the four appointments.
</P>
<P>
The appointment of Andrew K.N. Li as chief justice of the CFA
won unanimous support on May 24 at the provisional legislature.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
