<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0069 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Profiles: Litton, Ching, Bokhary, Recommended as Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Justices Litton, Ching and
Bokhary were recommended here today as permanent judges of Hong
Kong's Court of Final Appeal (CFA) after July 1.
</P>
<P>
The three recommendations still need to seek support from the
Provisional Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
Announcing these recommendations, Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
said: "The three judges recommended for appointment as permanent
judges of the CFA are all distinguished Justices of Appeal and
were outstanding legal practitioners before they joined the
bench."
</P>
<P>
He said, "With such an outstanding team, I am confident that
the Court of Final Appeal will play a pivotal role in the
development of Hong Kong's jurisprudence and legal system in the
years to come."
</P>
<P>
Litton, born in Hong Kong on August 7, 1934, received his
education in Hong Kong at Diocesan Boys' School, at King's College
Taunton and at Merton College, Oxford. He was awarded a Master of
Arts degree in Jurisprudence in 1956.
</P>
<P>
He practiced at the Hong Kong Bar from 1960. He was appointed
to the Court of Appeal in September 1992 and was appointed vice
president of the Court of Appeal in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Litton has written and published extensively on legal
subjects. He was the founder and editor-in-chief of the Hong Kong
Law Journal from 1970 to 1992. He is chairman of the Editorial
Advisory Board, Halsbury's Laws of Hong Kong. He is married with
six children.
</P>
<P>
Ching, born in Hong Kong on October 7, 1935, was educated in
Hong Kong at Diocesan Boys' School, King's College, Taunton and at
University College, Oxford. He was awarded a Bachelor of Arts
degree in Jurisprudence in 1957.
</P>
<P>
He was in private practice until his appointment as a justice
of the Court of Appeal in July 1995.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Ching served as chairman of the Hong Kong Bar
Association, president of the Poisons and Pharmacy Appeals
Tribunal, deputy chairman of the Inland Revenue Board of review
and of the Criminal Injuries Compensation Board. He is married
with three daughters.
</P>
<P>
Bokhary, born on October 25, 1947, received his education in
Hong Kong at King George V School and his legal education in
England. He was admitted to the Hong Kong Bar in 1971.
</P>
<P>
He was in private practice in Hong Kong and appeared before the
Privy Council in London until his appointment as a High Court
judge in March 1989. He was appointed a justice of the Court of
Appeal in March 1993.
</P>
<P>
Bokhary is president of the Deportation Tribunal and chairman
of the Civil Court Users Committee. He is a member of the Law
Faculty of the City University of Hong Kong and the Editorial
Advisory Board of Halsbury's Laws of Hong Kong. He is married with
three daughters. 
</P>
