<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Further Develop Ties with Pakistan: Zno </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Visiting South African Foreign
Minister Alfred B. Zno said here today that there is tremendous
potential for further development of the Pakistan-South African
relations.
</P>
<P>
Zno said the bilateral relations between South Africa and
Pakistan were growing well. And still there exited much potential
for the two countries to develop their ties, particularly in
economic and trade areas, he added.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference at the Foreign Ministry, Zno
said that he had broad-ranging discussions this morning with his
Pakistani counterpart Gohar Ayub Khan.
</P>
<P>
