<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Implement Integrated Service Digital Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam will start using integrated
service digital network (isdn) to replace the existing integrated
digital network (idn) from now to 1998 in the national post and
telecommunications network.
</P>
<P>
With isdn technology, subscribers will use various services
including facsimile, data, video sound and voice.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's telecommunications industry is now growing at 22-30
per cent each year with the telephone system reaching 64 percent
of total communes nationwide and phone use averaging 1.56 phones
per hundred people.
</P>
<P>
The industry is striving to reach 1,440 million minutes of
domestic phone calls and 330 million minutes of foreign phone
calls this year. 
</P>
