<HEADLINE> Teenager Pregnancy in Uganda at 43 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's teenager pregnancy rate
of 43 percent is the highest in sub-Sahara Africa, a gender and
community development officer said here yesterday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Monitor today, Rose Nalwadda told a workshop,
organized by the Uganda Parliamentary Forum on Food Security,
Population and Development, that 30 percent of the 17-year-old
females in Uganda have been pregnant at least once, and 25
percent of all the adolescent pregnancies end in illegal abortion.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen percent of births belong to women under the age of
20, she added.
</P>
<P>
She told her audience that 68 percent of girls and 75 percent
of boys between 15 and 19 have sex.
</P>
<P>
She attributed adolescence pregnancy to the high mortality and
morbidity rate. 
</P>
