<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Lebanese Visitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen said today that China supports Lebanon's
position on the implementation of the No. 425 resolution of the
Security Council of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remark here this afternoon when talking about the
Middle East issue in meeting with Zafer el-Hassan,
secretary-general of the Foreign Ministry of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China holds that the Mid-East peace process
should continue in accordance with the principle of "land for
peace" and on the basis of relevant resolutions of the UN.
</P>
<P>
Parties concerned should resume their peace talks on the basis
of the progress already made till the eventual realization of an
overall and just peace in the Middle East, added Qian.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the realization of peace in the region is
not only in the fundamental interests of the peoples of all
countries there, but also conducive to world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations, Qian said that since China established
diplomatic relations with Lebanon 26 years ago, bilateral friendship
and cooperation in various fields have developed smoothly with the
efforts of the leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two countries share identical or similar views on major
international and regional issues, and have supported each other
and conducted good cooperation in international and bilateral
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Qian also asked Hassan to convey his regards to Lebanese
Foreign Minister Farez Bweiz.
</P>
<P>
Conveying a greeting from Bweiz to Qian, Hassan said that the
Lebanese government congratulates China on the upcoming return of
Hong Kong, reiterating that his country adheres to a "one China"
stand and supports China's great cause of reunification.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese government is satisfied with the steady
development of bilateral relations, added Hassan.
</P>
<P>
He said that Lebanon appreciates Chinese government's
consistent support for the Mid-East peace process, noting that
the Lebanese people long for peace.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon hopes to continue peace talks in accordance with the
principles formulated in relevant resolutions of the UN and by the
Madrid peace conference, so as to ensure an effective
implementation of the No. 425 resolution of the UN Security
Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
