<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline in dull trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index fell by 2.81 points to close at
1,990.68 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was still thin at 101.33 million units,
worth 295.38 million Singapore dollars (about 206.56 million US
dollars). Declines led advances by 187 to 102, while 336 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of almost eight million units. It was
followed by HuanHsin which had 4.88 million of shares traded. The
Raffles Medical Group was next with 3.66 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) led the gainers of the day
as it rose by 30 cents to finish at 12.5 Singapore dollars. Local
property developer City Developments gained 20 cents to end at
13.8 Singapore dollars, while Metro Holdings closed 18 cents
higher at 4.6 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the SPH Foreign was the biggest loser as it
declined by 90 cents to end at 28.3 Singapore dollars. Thai Prime
Fund fell by 50 cents to close at 8.5 US dollars, while the Asean
Fund, Creative 50 and the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign lost
40 cents each to finish at 16.6 US dollars, 22.3 Singapore dollars
and 15.3 Singapore dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
