<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Under heavy fire, French soldiers Wednesday continued to
evacuate foreigners from Congo Republic, where armed clash
intensified between the Congolese army and the militiamen of former
President Sassou N'Guesso, despite an appeal for ceasefire by
President Pascal Lissouba.
</P>
<P>
-- The European Commission's president Jacques Santer will
present today to French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin a package of
compromise proposals on revising the Stability Pact for the European
single currency, which includes the establishment of an ``economic
pole'' by the economy ministers of European countries to
counterbalance the power of a future European central bank, as well
as a common policy on employment for European Union members.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- French Interior Minister Jean-Pierre Chevenement has expressed
indignation over an announcement by officials of the prime
minister's office that 40,000 paperless immigrants could be granted
the right to stay in France. He said that the announcement could
have a ``disastrous effect'' and would undermine the country's laws
on nationality and immigration.
</P>
<P>
-- British scientists have found that among women, the chromosome
X coming from their fathers has a stronger impact upon their
development of intelligence than that coming from their mothers. The
researchers hailed that for the first time, they have discovered the
different role played on genes by sex. 
</P>
</TEXT>
