<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Increase in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A total of 8,211 traffic accidents
recorded in the first five months this year killed 2,463 people
and injured 9,182 more in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
These figures were higher than that in the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, in the first half of 1995
traffic accident caused 17 deaths per day.
</P>
<P>
In August 1995, thanks to the implementation of a government
decree on traffic order, the number of traffic accidents dropped
registering an average of 11 deaths per day.
</P>
<P>
But since November 1995 the figure has increased to about 16
per day.
</P>
<P>
Main reasons include the rapidly growing number of vehicles on
the road and careless driving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
