<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor to Attend UN Special Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Song Jian will,
at the head of the Chinese Government Delegation, attend the 19th
Special Session of the United Nations General Assembly to be held
in New York from June 20 to 27.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Cui Tiankai made this remark at a
routine press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Cui noted that Song is also chairman of the Committee on
Environmental Protection of the State Council and minister in
charge of the State Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
The session is convened in accordance with the Agenda of the
21st Century adopted by the 1992 UN Conference on the Environment
and Development and with the provisions of relevant resolutions of
the UN General Assembly, the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
