<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Offers 1.5-Billion Yuan Loans for Aviation Technology Upgrading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) has signed
an agreement with the China Aviation Technology Import and Export
Corporation, to provide loans totaling 1.5 billion yuan (180.7
million US dollars) for the enterprise as circulation funds for
the rest of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The loans will ensure capital support for the company's major
projects, and the interest rate will be in line with the standard
set by the People's Bank of China, the central bank, instead of
being raised, according to Zhao Ange, vice-president of BOC.
</P>
<P>
In July 1996, China's State Economic and Trade Commission
(SETC) issued a circular to banks urging them to implement the
policy of assisting 300 key state-owned enterprises. The China
Aviation Technology Import and Export Corporation was one of those
300 enterprises and it was covered by BOC.
</P>
<P>
Since the corporation was set up in 1979, BOC has granted it
loans to the tune of some 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion US
dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
