<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan's Crown Prince Leaves for US, Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 12 (Xinhua) - Jordan's Crown Prince Hassan leaves
here this morning for official trips to the U.S., Turkey and some
European countries.
</P>
<P>
During his trip to the U.S., the second one within this year,
Hassan will discuss with U.S. President Bill Clinton and other
senior officials means of strengthening economic cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The talks will also cover U.S. support for economic projects in
Jordan, especially the Social Productivity Package which Jordan
adopted in March as a comprehensive plan to improve the quality
of life for all the Jordanians and develop infrastructure in some
areas.
</P>
<P>
Hassan will also hold talks with senior officials at the
U.S. State and Defense Departments.
</P>
<P>
On Hassan's way to Washington, he will pay a one-day visit to
Turkey where he will discuss with Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel, Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan and Foreign Minister
Tansu Ciller the Turkish military incursion into northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
On May 27, Jordan officially called on Turkey to pull
its troops immediately out of northern Iraq, saying its thrust
into Iraq to fight Kurdish rebels was a violation of Iraqi
sovereignty and a threat to its territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
The countries of Hassan's European tour have not been
disclosed yet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
