<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First Museum of Coastal Defense History Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Zhenhaikou Coastal Defense
History Museum, the first of its kind in China, opened in Zhenhai
in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The museum is designed to improve patriotism education among
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Zhenhai, located at the eastern tip of Zhejiang Province, was a
strategic point and witnessed Chinese people's heroic struggles
against Japanese, British and French invaders.
</P>
<P>
The museum, covering an area of 20,000 square meters,
features wars against foreign aggressors.
</P>
<P>
It was built on the southern side of the Zhaobao Mountain where
Chinese soldiers and local residents fought a fierce battle
against British invaders.
</P>
<P>
The museum cost 18 million yuan (2.1 million US dollars), 10.5
million of which was donated by institutes or individuals.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the ruins of the Zhenhai coastal defense fort
near the museum has opened following repair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Asked to Study Defense Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese people should be aware
of the National Defense Law, a government notice said.
</P>
<P>
The notice, jointly issued by the Propaganda Department of the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, the Ministry of Justice
and the General Political Department of the People's Liberation
Army, said that departments at different levels should attach
great importance to publicizing and studying the law.
</P>
<P>
The move is important for safeguarding national security, and
transforming China into a lawful society, the notice said, adding
that young people and cadres will be targeted first in the
program.
</P>
<P>
China's National Defense Law was approved in March 1997 at the
annual session of the National People's Congress, the country's
legislature. 
</P>
</TEXT>
