<HEADLINE> Chinese Border Province Opens Wider </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan Province, bordering
Vietnam, in southwest China, has forged trade relations with 87
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
To date, the province has approved 1,468 overseas-backed
enterprises, involving 830 million US dollars in overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
It handled imports and exports worth 2.06 billion US dollars
last year, contributing about 15 percent to its gross domestic
product, said Li Xun, deputy secretary-general of the Provincial
Society of International Trade.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan has launched 56 projects involving the use of foreign
loans topping one billion US dollars. So far, 27 projects have
been completed.
</P>
<P>
A Hong Kong investment company purchased the authority to
operate Shilin-Anning super-highway last year, opening a new
channel for introducing overseas capital for local infrastructure
construction.
</P>
<P>
With approval from central authorities, the provincial capital
city of Kunming has opened its financial sector to the outside
world. As a result, the Krung Thai Bank Public Company, Ltd.,
Kunming, the first overseas-financed bank in the city, has opened
in Kunming.
</P>
<P>
Some Southeast Asian countries such as Thailand and the Laos
have set up general consulates in Kunming, and the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council has also opened a representative office there.
</P>
<P>
China's Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation has
established a commissioner's office in the city to provide
services for foreign trade business in the whole of southwest
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
