<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, ASEAN Viewed as South Korea's Prime Competitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 12 (Xinhua) -- South Korean export companies see
China and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) as
the most formidable competitors in international trade markets, a
survey on local trade firms has shown.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey conducted by the Korea International
Trade Association (KITA) on 1,000 export firms in 33 business
categories, 34 percent of them hold this view.
</P>
<P>
This represents a sharp contrast with past trends when the
newly industrialized countries and areas (NICA) like Singapore,
Taiwan and Hong Kong were the strongest rivals for South Korea.
</P>
<P>
About 27 percent of the questioned in the current survey viewed
the NICA as the most powerful competitors to be followed by Japan.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the competitiveness of South Korea's export
commodities, 53 percent said that they have less advantage
compared with their rivals.
</P>
<P>
Some respondents said the weaker competitiveness of South
Korea's export goods is due to higher price and lower quality.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
