<HEADLINE> Chinese Students Asked to Provide Service for Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government is calling
on students throughout China to go to countryside this summer and
provide services for farmers.
</P>
<P>
A notice issued here today by the Propaganda Department of the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and other departments
said that students should voluntarily help wipe out illiteracy,
give artistic performances, provide scientific instruction and
medical care for farmers.
</P>
<P>
The notice said that the "Go to Countryside Program", which
will be carried out during July and August, would provide very
significant experiences to the youngsters.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,000 teams will be organized to help farmers learn to
read, while 1,000 doctors and master degree students are expected
to join in a poverty-relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, students will make an investigation into the
health conditions of one million farmers during the summer
vocation, the notice added.  
