<HEADLINE> Chronicle of Late Premier Zhou Enlai's Life Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The "Chronicle of Zhou Enlai's
Life," covering his time 1949 to 1976, has been published by
the Central Literature Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The three-volume chronicle, 1.56 million characters in length,
was compiled by the Party Literature Research Center of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The set of books provide comprehensive and accurate details
relevant to the biographical study of the highly-respected late
Chinese premier, as well as facts on the history of the Communist
Party and the country since the founding of the People's Republic
of China in 1949, compilers said.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Enlai, regarded as an outstanding thinker and contributor
to Mao Zedong Thought, achieved much in the fields of politics,
military and foreign affairs, economics, united front work against
Japanese aggression, science and technology, education, and
literature and arts.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that studying Zhou's philosophy is also of great
significance when adhering to Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, carrying out the Party's
basic line and principles, and forming a correct outlook on the
world, life and human values. 
</P>
</TEXT>
