<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central China Province to Step up Biodiversity Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
will cooperate with Finland to implement an action plan to promote
biodiversity.
</P>
<P>
At a recent conference in Changsha, capital of the province,
some 100 experts from both China and Europe discussed how to
protect the rare plants and animals in the province.
</P>
<P>
Hunan boasts one of the richest biodiversities in the world. It
has the largest subtropical evergreen broadleaf forest at the
latitude. It is home to more than 4,400 varieties of identified
advanced plants and over 26 percent of the country's vertebrate
wildlife species.
</P>
<P>
So far, the province has set up 33 nature reserves and worked
out a series of wildlife protection rules and policies.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Department of Forestry set up a joint committee
with its Finnish counterpart in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
