<HEADLINE> New Airport For East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- construction of a new airport that
is capable of accomodating large planes has been finished in
Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
A airbus 300-600 landed safely at the new airport yesterday
afternoon, putting an end to Nanjing's past history of not being
able to handle big planes.
</P>
<P>
The new airport is located in Lukou Town, Jiangning County.
Construction of the airport began in February 1995 and the airport
passed joint assessment of East China Administration of Civil
Aviation and Jiangsu Province on June 2 this year.
</P>
<P>
It has built necessary advanced facilities, including a runway
which is 3,600 m long and 60 m wide, which enables this airport to
handle Boeing 747-400 planes.
</P>
<P>
The whole project cost 2.372 billion yuan, which was provided
by the Civil Aviation Administration of China, Jiangsu Provincial
Government, Nanjing City Government and some loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
