<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second IMS-GT Ministerial Meeting Held in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia today urged the
governments in the Indonesia-Malaysia-Singapore Growth Triangle
(IMS-GT) to play a pro-active role in promoting investment and
trade cross-flows within the region.
</P>
<P>
The main objective is to have a focused approach in
implementing ASEAN regional and sub-regional cooperation and
integration and to realize the optimum benefits of public-private
sector partnerships, Malaysian International Trade and Industry
Minister Rafidah Aziz told the Second IMS-GT Ministerial Meeting.
</P>
<P>
The one-day meeting was being held in Johor Baharu, 370 km
southeast of the capital. Singapore's Minister of Trade and
Industry Lee Yock Suan and Indonesia's Coordinating Minister for
Production and Distribution Hartarto were attending the meeting,
the Malaysian national news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
Rafidah said there must be a coherent and systematic management
of the economic synergy and the business communities of the
sub-region must benefit from such an effort.
</P>
<P>
Within the context of Pan ASEAN trade liberalization and
investment facilitation, the sub-regional public-private sector
initiatives should assume the necessary catalystic role in moving
forward such objectives, she said.
</P>
<P>
She said the experience of the business community operating at
the sub-regional can provide an impetus to the respective
governments to continually monitor policies and procedures so as
to make for enhanced transparency, predictability and credibility.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN commitment to evolve a dynamic and liberal ASEAN Free
Trade Area (AFTA) and an attractive and competitive ASEAN
Investment Area should be realized and operationalized at the
sub-regional level in the most effective way, she said.
</P>
<P>
Borders within the sub-region can virtually be eliminated and
cross-border resource flows and activities could be significantly
promoted, she added.
</P>
<P>
"Within the IMS-GT sub-region, each individual constituent
member becomes the other's economic hinterland and provides each
other with the complementing inputs for optimizing economic
resource mobilization and assisting in individual development
objectives," Rafidah said.
</P>
<P>
She said the IMS-GT could make for a more balanced distribution
of growth and development benefits as well as exploiting the
economic potential of the areas in the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
Today's IMS-GT ministerial meeting provided a good opportunity
for the three neighbors to review the present status of
cooperation within the triangle in efforts to further consolidate
economic linkages.
</P>
<P>
The IMS-GT, formerly known as the Singapore-johor-Riau (SIJORI)
Growth Triangle, covers Singapore, West Sumatera in Indonesia, and
Malaysia's states of Pahang, Negeri Sembilan and Melaka (Malacca).
</P>
<P>
It has emerged as a viable ASEAN investment area. Malaysian
businessmen have benefited greatly from reverse investments in
Sumatera, Indonesia, and this has been the same for Singapore,
whose investments in Malaysia have been growing.
</P>
<P>
The governments of Malaysia, Indonesia and Singapore are making
everything effort to facilitate cross-border investments in the
IMS-GT.
</P>
<P>
Any growth in the triangle could serve as a model for other
triangles in the ASEAN region and for cooperation on a global
basis, observers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0129 </DOCNO>
