<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Be More Prosperous After Return: Statesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will become more
prosperous under the principle of "one country, two systems" after
its return to China on July 1 this year, a senior Japanese
statesman said.
</P>
<P>
Hata Tsutomu, former Japanese prime minister and president of
the Japanese Dietmen's League For Japan-Hong Kong, told Chinese
reporters recently that China's resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong is an event of great significance in
the contemporary world.
</P>
<P>
China has settled the issue of Hong Kong, a thorny one
concerning national sovereignty, through negotiations with
Britain, in which the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping played an
outstanding role, said Tsutomu, who is also the leader of Japan's
Sun Party.
</P>
<P>
He noted that politically, the appropriate solution of the Hong
Kong issue depends on the concept of "one country, two systems,"
initiated by Deng.
</P>
<P>
"I have heartfelt esteem for Mr. Deng Xiaoping's insight,
wisdom and decision," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the prospects of Hong Kong after the return, he said it will
maintain its position as the financial center and entrepot of
Asia, and its stability and prosperity beneficial to China as well
as to Asia and the whole world.
</P>
<P>
The successful solution to the Hong Kong issue will contribute
to the final reunification of China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tsutomu said that as a genuine friend of China, he will go to
Hong Kong to attend celebrations marking its return to China and
to witness the great moment and feel its historical significance
himself. 
</P>
</TEXT>
