<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Branch of China's Largest Bank Reports Record Deposits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fuzhou, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Savings deposits at the Fujian
Provincial Branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
(ICBC), the country's largest bank, has been growing at an annual
rate of more than 10 billion yuan (about 1.2 billion US dollars)
in the past three years.
</P>
<P>
The lastest statistics show that the branch had outstanding
savings deposits of 58.7 billion yuan at the end of May, the
largest among all local banks.
</P>
<P>
A bank official said that the effort to offer a broader range
of intermediate services and agent services was a major reason for
the substantial increase in the deposit amount.
</P>
<P>
A rapidly expanding electronic service network, which has been
extended to 16 large and medium-sized cities outside the province,
has also made the branch a magnet for savings deposits, the
official explained.
</P>
<P>
As the income of Chinese residents increases as a result of the
country's economic boom, the total amount of savings deposits in
China has surged in recent years. Official figures show that the
total outstanding savings deposits in China have exceeded four
trillion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
