<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Levies Anti-dumping Duties on Newsprint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- India's Commerce Ministry has
recommended the imposition of provisional anti-dumping duty on
newsprint from the United States, Canada and Russia, the Indian
Express said today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has given its recommendation to the Finance
Ministry, which is expected to issue a notification to this effect
soon.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Ministry had initiated investigations in December
last year into charges of dumping newsprint by the U.S., Canada
and Russia.
</P>
<P>
The charges, made by the domestic newsprint makers, said that
the three countries were exporting newsprint to India at prices
below normal.
</P>
<P>
In a petition to the Commerce Ministry, the Indian Newsprint
Manufacturers Association said that the export of cheap newsprint
by these countries was causing "material injury" to them.
</P>
<P>
The ministry after making preliminary investigations reached a
conclusion that newsprint "originating or imported" from the three
countries was indeed being sold in India at below normal value.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
