<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest Chinese Region To Build Largest Wolfberry Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
in northwest China plans to build its area to divert water from
the Yellow River into the country's largest Chinese wolfberry
production base.
</P>
<P>
Wolfberry, a special product in Ningxia, is known as a
nutritious Chinese medicinal herb.
</P>
<P>
The base will cover more than 3,300 ha of farmland, and is
expected to produce over 60 million yuan of output value annually
upon completion.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic region is to invest 55 million yuan in building a
wolfberry garden, a seedling raising base, a new variety breeding
base, a new technology spreading system, and some deep processing
projects.
</P>
<P>
To promote a rising pillar industry, the regional government
has set up a leading body as well as a group of experts to take
charge of the construction of the wolfberry production base, and
has signed contracts with eight counties and cities involved to
ensure the smooth construction of the base. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
