<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea's Hyundai Ranks World's 11th Vehicle Seller </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 12 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's Hyundai Motor Company
ranked 11th in vehicles sales in the world in 1996, statistics of
the 1997 world auto market show.
</P>
<P>
The leading US auto magazine "Automotive News" has reported
that Hyundai sold 1.31 million vehicles last year, ahead of
Peugeot, BMW, Mercedes-Benz, Mazda and Volvo.
</P>
<P>
Hyundai occupied 13th place in 1995 with sales of 1.16 million
units.
</P>
<P>
"It is rare for an automaker to jump over two places in the
ranking in one year in such competitive world auto market," said
an official of the Korea Automobile Manufacturers Association
(KAMA).
</P>
<P>
Hyundai is expected to join the top 10 of the world vehicle
sellers by the year 2000, a Hyundai official said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, General Motors Corp. (GM) topped the list with 8.38
million units, followed by Ford Motor Co. with 6.65 million units
and Toyota Motor Corp. with 4.07 million units.
</P>
<P>
North America took the first place with 16.65 million units,
followed by Western Europe with 14.48 million units and the
Asia-Pacific region with 13.66 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
