<HEADLINE> Life Insurance Booming in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- This, China's largest trade and
financial center, has generated a total of 1.29 billion yuan (155
million US Dollars) in life insurance premium income in the first
quarter of this year, which indicates a bright future for local
life insurance business.
</P>
<P>
The figure was up 122 percent from the same period of last
year. The city sold only 2.6 billion yuan-worth (313 million US
dollars) life insurance policies last year.
</P>
<P>
Insurance experts said that the rapid growth of Shanghai's life
insurance market is attributed to the growing awareness of local
residents in life insurance.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey conducted by the Shanghai Insurance Institute
shows that 80 percent of locals are planning to buy life
insurance, and 15 percent of Shanghai people have done that before.
</P>
<P>
"Most of them think that they should have more ways to
counteract life risks, and commercial insurance have been taken as
a way for long-term investment by local residents," experts said.
</P>
<P>
Now there are some 20,000 life insurance sales agents serving
across the city, and commercial life insurance has become an
integral part of the daily life of local people.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is also one of the only two cities open to overseas
investors. The other is Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The municipality's life premium income edged up with that
generated in local property insurance industry last year, both
accounting for 49.6 percent of the city's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
