<HEADLINE> hke061215-- Vietnamese Illegal Immigrants Return to Hanoi From HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-six Vietnamese illegal
immigrants returned by air to Hanoi, Vietnam today on the 106th
flight under the Orderly Repatriation Program (ORP).
</P>
<P>
The returnees comprised 63 men, one woman and two boys. Most
of them are from the northern part of Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the returnees arrived in Hong Kong this year. A
few came last year.
</P>
<P>
The group brought to 10,610 the total number repatriated on ORP
flights since November 1991.  
</P>
</TEXT>
