<HEADLINE> India's Congress Party Poll Results Expected Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Counting of votes for the post
of the Congress Party president will begin here at the All India
Congress Committee (AICC) headquarters at 11:00 a.m. local time
today, the newspaper National Herald reported.
</P>
<P>
During the poll held on June 9, incumbent Congress Party
President Sitaram Kesri, Congress Party leader in the Lok Sabha
(the lower house of parliament) Sharad Pawar and another senior
party leader Rajesh Pilot were contending for the post.
</P>
<P>
According to the Congress Party sources, all ballot boxes had
been brought and kept in the hall of the party headquarters here.
All arrangements had been made for the counting of votes.
</P>
<P>
Over 8,000 Congress Party delegates, mainly party leaders at
different levels across the country, took part in the exercise on
June 9.
</P>
<P>
It is widely believed here that Kesri will be re-elected
president of the 112-year-old party.  
</P>
</TEXT>
