<HEADLINE> El Salvador Fined over Crowd Trouble </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 11 (Xinhua) -- El Salvador was finded 35,000
U.S. dollars by FIFA for an outbreak of crowd trouble during last
weekend's World Cup qualifier against Mexico.
</P>
<P>
"El Salvador presented FIFA with evidence to show that there
was no reason to punish the Salvadorean authorities," the the
Salvadorean Football Federation said in a statement on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
After the Mexico game, hundreds of home fans, angry at the
result which saw the visitors won 1-0 and several refereeing
decisions against its team, began throwing plastic water bottles
and cans at visiting players, forcing police to intervene, a
report said reaching here.
</P>
<P>
FIFA also ruled that El Salvador's Serbian coach Milovan
D'Joric must serve a two-match suspension as well as pay a 5,000
U.S. dollars fine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
