<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Killed by Police in West Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Three persons were killed and
several injured in western Nepali district of Nawalparasi when
police opened fire to disperse a group of agitating locals, press
reports here said today.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy happened when a group of children playing at the
roadside threw a dead snake on a bus packed with policemen
returning from their assignment at the local election Monday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The policemen got off and arrested two brothers aged 21 and 23
respectively, who happened to be on the spot.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the two brothers were ruthlessly beaten by the
policemen inside the bus. They both died the next day.
</P>
<P>
Outraged by the inhuman act of the policemen, the local people
burned a police post and demanded that guilty policemen be handed
to them.
</P>
<P>
The policemen opened fire and killed a traveler on the spot.
</P>
<P>
Two men involved in the demonstration were severely hit on the
head by the policemen. They fell unconscious and were taken away
by the policemen. Their whereabouts are still not known. One woman
is also missing since then.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Home Ministry confirmed the death of the two
brothers and the unidentified traveler.
</P>
<P>
The opposition Nepali Congress Wednesday expressed "deep
concern" over the incident and demanded that the government
compensate the family of the dead and treat the injured.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
