<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Serbia Holds Exhibition on Return of Hong Kong to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A picture show on the return of
Hong Kong to China was held in Novi Sad, capital of Vojvodina
Autonomous Province in the Serbian Republic today.
</P>
<P>
Vojvodina Vice Prime Minister D. Radenkov said today at the
opening ceremony that the return of Hong Kong to the motherland is
of great historic significance. The return has resulted from the
long time unremitting efforts for peaceful settlement of the Hong
Kong issue made by the Chinese government and Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government made great efforts on the smooth
transition of Hong Kong. The transition is not only of historic
significance to China, but also of broad international
significance in the whole world, Radenkov said.
</P>
<P>
The peaceful settlement of Hong Kong is a model of the
solutions to disputes through long and patient negotiations. The
vice prime minister said the traditional friendship between the
Yugoslav and Chinese people has experienced historical tests. "We
will share the happy moment with the Chinese People."
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Yugoslavia Zhu Ankang said that the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland is a great event both to
China and the world. It does not only mean an end to an era and
the beginning of a new century in Hong Kong, but also an important
step for the Chinese people to realize reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
About 100 pictures on the British invasion in Hong Kong and the
long struggle for the transition were on display at the show.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will last until June 20 and then go on to other
cities in Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
