<HEADLINE> 200 Evacuated over Volcanic Eruption in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Over 200 people have been
evacuated from the area around Mount Karangetang on Siau Island in
Indonesia's North Sulawesi province, where volcanic eruption
continued to spew clouds of hot ash and lava, local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Evacuations were carried out from Tatahadeng village on the
upper slopes of the volcano to the town of Ulu on the eastern side
of the island, local official Oka Makagansa was quoted as saying
last night.
</P>
<P>
The 1,784-meter high volcano erupted wildly Sunday leaving
three people dead.
</P>
<P>
Volcanic hot steam clouds can reach temperatures of 600 degrees
Celsius, destroying almost anything in their path.
</P>
<P>
Lava and hot clouds of steam were still bursting out of the
volcano Wednesday, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Minor eruptions have been happening since April 19.
</P>
<P>
Mount Karangetang is one of the most active volcanoes on the
islands. Six people in the village of Dame near the volcano died
in a similar eruption in 1992, reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
