<HEADLINE> Finnish Official Outlines New Geopolitical World Map </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A senior Finnish official today
sketched out a new geopolitical map for the world in early next
century with China, the European Union, the United States, Japan
and India as the main economic powers.
</P>
<P>
Alpo Rusi, a special advisor to Finnish president Martti
Ahtisaari, said at a conference held here by the Finnish Promoting
European Security Commission that the world will see four or five
major economic regions in the period of 2010-2015.
</P>
<P>
He expected that the EU and the U.S. should be united to
compete with the new Asian economic powers, while the EU should
promote, together with Russia, the gradual integration of Europe.
</P>
<P>
Tarja Halonen, Finnish foreign minister, told the conference
that following the signing of the document on their relations,
NATO and Russia should share their views on benefits for enlarging
the NATO peaceful partnership and not carve out spheres of
influence in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Halonen stressed it was a natural outcome for Finland to join
the Euro-Atlantic Partnership Council of NATO which is in a
continued expansion process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
