<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fifty-five Million Chinese Families Get Relief Aids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A government official revealed
here today that some 55 million Chinese families, have benefitted
from a government-sponsored disaster-relief fund over the past 14
years.
</P>
<P>
Li Bengong, who is in charge of disaster-relief work at the
Ministry of Civil Affairs, said that 30 million of the families
which suffered from floods, earthquakes and other misfortunes have
got rid of poverty after receiving government subsidies.
</P>
<P>
He said that the country has poured some 1.1 billion yuan (some 130
million US dollars) every year to help these families since it set
up a disaster-relief foundation in 1983.
</P>
<P>
The money did not include the amount directly allocated by the
central government to cover the losses caused by particular
disasters, he said, adding that some 2.3 billion yuan (nearly 300
million US dollars) were allocated and about half of it were spent in
this respect last year.
</P>
<P>
The country has created 24,000 organizations to manage the use
of the disaster-relief fund, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
