<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Greets Philippine Independence Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Qian
Qichen today congratulated his Philippine counterpart Domingo
Siazon on the 99th anniversary of the independence of the
Philippines and expressed his hope for closer bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
During the 22 years of established ties, "the friendly and
cooperative relations in all fields ... have seen continuous
consolidation and development," Qian said in a message.
</P>
<P>
"I am ready to work together with you for the establishment of
the 21-century-oriented good-neighborly relationship of friendship
and cooperation between China and the Philippines," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines declared independence on June 12, 1898 when the
United States, winning a war with Spain, took over the territory
after its three centuries under Spanish rule.
</P>
<P>
In World War II, the Philippines fell into Japan's occupation.
After the war it remained under the United States' control until
gaining independence on July 4, 1946. 
</P>
</TEXT>
