<HEADLINE> Shanghai Promotes Non-governmental Theatrical Troupes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- To help enrich cultural life,
Shanghai, China's most important commercial center, has given a
big boost to non-governmental theatrical troupes.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 30 such troupes have been active in
Shanghai's theaters, following the rule of the market economy and
suiting different tastes of the audience, sources revealed.
</P>
<P>
They receive no subsidies from government finance, and are
fully responsible for their own losses and benefits. They gave
1,500 performances to 488,000 residents last year.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1950s, all cultural troupes in China had been run by
governments at different levels.
</P>
<P>
The newly-encouraged theatrical troupes are part of the current
reform of the cultural system nationwide aiming at introducing
competition into the sector.
</P>
<P>
The first group of non-governmental troupes appeared mainly in
coastal cities and provinces like Shanghai and Guangdong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
