<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Chile's Economy Minister Alvaro
Garcia said today he is happy with Hong Kong's return to China and
promised to maintain closer ties with China as well as its new
special administrative region.
</P>
<P>
"I feel happy about Hong Kong's return to the People's Republic
of China, not just because of what it means to the Chinese people
but also because the procedure used to obtain that objective
constitutes an example of modern diplomatic practice," Garcia
said.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Garcia said Chile will continue
its efforts to maintain close links with China and its Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
