<HEADLINE> France Draws with Italy 2-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 11, (Xinhua) -- Two goals from forwards Zinedine
Zidane and Youri Djorkaeff earned France a 2-2 draw Wednesday with
Italy and saved the host team finishing third in the Tournoi de
France.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Alessandro del Pier equalized in the last minute for
Italy, converting a penalty that made him top scorer in the
exhibition event with three goals in as many games.
</P>
<P>
Italy was undone by another Italian-based star when Inter
Milan's Djorkaeff came on as substitute and quickly made his
mark. He took a short pass in the 73rd minute and sent a scorching
drive from some 25 meters crashing high into the right corner of
Gianluca Pagliuca's goal.
</P>
<P>
But in the last minute, Lilian Thuram brought down del Piero in
the penalty area and the Juventus striker converted the spot kick
himself to earn Italy the draw.
</P>
<P>
England had been assured of victory in the four-nation event
since last Sunday and Brazil clinched second place with a 1-0 win
over England Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
England totaled six points, ahead of Brazil with five. France
and Italy both totaled two points but France took third place
because of a better goal differential.  
</P>
</TEXT>
