<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Citizens Work To Make Their City Greener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, Jane 12 (Xinhua) -- Citizens in south China's
Guangzhou city are now making redoubled efforts to green their
home place.
</P>
<P>
Last year some 1.8 million people in Guangzhou turned out to
plant more than 2 million trees in both parks and suburban areas
of the city.
</P>
<P>
In downtown Guangzhou, people can often see such watchwords
written in big Chinese characters saying "planting three to five
trees every year is an obligation of every able bodied citizen."
</P>
<P>
China has for long promoted tree-planting activities. In
Baiyun (white cloud) Mountain, a well-known tourist site in
suburban Guangzhou, a large piece of land was designated to
planting trees in memory of one's dead dear ones.
</P>
<P>
In the nine years since the memorial forest park was
established, thousands of families have come to plant trees to
cherish the memory of the dead.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a number of other kinds of memorial forests like
"youth forest" and "lover's forest" have been organized within the
city's administrative area. 
