<HEADLINE> Northwest China Gas to Be Piped To Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Facilities for piping gas from oil
fields in the central Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia basin of northwest
China to Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi Province, have been completed
and are now ready for operation.
</P>
<P>
The project, with a daily supply capacity of 170,000 cu m, has
been undertaken by the Changqing Petroleum Prospecting
Administration based in Jingbian county of northern Shaanxi.
</P>
<P>
Gas is scheduled to be piped to this cultural and historical
city on July 1, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, gas from oilfields of the same
region is also expected to be piped to Beijing and Tianjin in
September this year on the completion of another major pipeline
project involving an investment of 3.3 billion yuan and with a
total length of nearly 1,000 km. 
</P>
