<HEADLINE> Argentine President Stresses Importance of Educational Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos
Menem stressed today the importance of a revolutionary change in
education in order to meet the world's demands.
</P>
<P>
At a university ceremony, Menem also criticized those who are
opposed to educational reforms.
</P>
<P>
He said that a revolution in education "is what is occurring in
all countries on this planet" and even small countries have become
stronger after young people received better education.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the "new proposal for education" to which
impetus has been given is to perfect management of human resources
in this country, so that Argentina can catch up with the
development of science and technology, particularly computer
technology in the world.
</P>
<P>
But the proposal has been opposed by teachers and students, who
have held demonstrations against charging school registration fees
and modifications in subject curriculums.
</P>
<P>
At today's ceremony, Menem gave the award of "Presidency of the
Nation" to 33 university students who gained the highest grades in
their study. 
</P>
