<HEADLINE> Central China Province Gets Good Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 12 (Xinhua) -- North China's Henan Province has
got a record summer grain harvest of 23.684 billion kilos this
year, a rise of 15.4 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
A provincial agricultural official said that rising grain
purchase price by the state has boosted farmers' enthusiasm in
growing grain and that the province's grain growing area, at 4.997
million ha, set a record in 37 years.
</P>
<P>
The province's spreading of technology also has helped improve
the quality of soil and seeds, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the climatic condition is also much better than last
year, with much rainfall in spring. 
</P>
