<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningxia Developing Water-Saving Irrigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
in the upper and middle reaches of the Yellow River has made
notable progress in developing water-saving farm irrigation.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the northwest China region has long
been afflicted with shortage of water for agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
To enhance the water utilization rate, the region has invested
more than 40 million yuan in recent years to rebuild and renovate
83 irrigation projects.
</P>
<P>
So far, water-saving irrigation has covered over 160,000 ha of
farmland across the region, saving 300 million cu m of water
annually for agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
To rationally exploit water resources, the autonomous region
has stepped up efforts to develop new water resources, fully
tapping rainfall and underground water for farming purpose.
</P>
<P>
The region also introduced seeping and dripping irrigation on
nearly 10,000 ha of farmland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
