<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Powerful Earthquakes Hit Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A powerful earthquake
shook large areas of Colombia, including the capital, this
afternoon, said a spokesman for the National Seismological
Institute.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, measuring 6.2 on the Richter scale, struck at 2:13
p.m.local time (1913 GMT) and was felt across most of the country.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, another tremor, measuring 6 on the Richer scale,
jolted northeast Colombia at 2:07 a.m. local time, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
Both quakes were centered in a mountainous area about 40
kilometers southeast of Bucaramanga, the capital of northern
Santander province.
</P>
<P>
So far, there were no immediate reports of damage or injury.
</P>
</TEXT>
