<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Multi-Cropping Enhances Utilization Index of Arable Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong province has
effectively enhanced the utilization index of arable land by
developing the multi-purpose cultivation technology.
</P>
<P>
Shandong is a populous province with the average per capita
arable land lower than the national average. The province loses
over 33,000 ha of arable land on a year-on-year basis for various
reasons.
</P>
<P>
To make up for the shortage of arable land resources, the
province has tried every means possible to raise land utilization
index and and the per unit grain yield.
</P>
<P>
The technology of multi-cropping has been widely applied the
province. The three-cropping areas have extended to 2 million ha.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the traditional seasonal agricultural production
circle of sowing in spring, harvesting in Autumn and land lying
idle in Winter has been changed.
</P>
<P>
Farm activities are as busy in the Winter, and in fact they are
going full steam ahead all the year round.
</P>
<P>
Winter warm houses are developing fast in Shandong, with 1.5
million such houses operational across the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
