<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali
Alatas and Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono will attend the
ceremony for Hong Kong's handover to China at the end of this
month, officials at the presidential palace said here today.
</P>
<P>
Alatas was invited as Indonesia's representative to a midnight
extravaganza, to be attended by 4,000 VIPs, including Chinese
President Jiang Zemin, said the officials. The handover marks the
end of 156 years of British colonial rule in Hong Kong.
</P>
