<HEADLINE> Mexican Volcano Spews out Ash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Volcanic ash rained down on
communities in southern Mexico today after the volcano near
Popocatepetl mountain in the southern state of Morelos
erupted.
</P>
<P>
Ramon Pena, director of the Popocatepetl Operation Program,
said ash spewed 5,000 meters into the air from volcano's crater.
</P>
<P>
He said that the main area affected by the rain was the town of
Tetela del Volcan, but residents were not at risk.
</P>
<P>
The volcano, located 60 kilometers southeast of Mexico City
became active again at the end of 1994. 
