<HEADLINE> Real Estate Management Firms in Shanghai Exceed 1,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- This cosmopolitan in east China
now has more than 1,000 real estate management firms, which have
employed a total of 30,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Breakdowns available show that assets of the 1,028 property
managerial firms in Shanghai, the country's largest industrial and
commercial center, had topped 11.4 billion yuan (1.37 billion US
dollars) by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises have become the backbone of the
municipality's property management force. Of the total, assets of
the state-owned enterprises account for 41.9 percent. And the
enterprises have employed 20,600 people.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, assets of companies of limited liability
comprise 17.7 percent, and assets of Sino-foreign joint ventures
and collectively-owned firms make up 8.7 percent and 7.6 percent
respectively. Employees of the firms total 16,100.
</P>
<P>
So far, the housing space under the managment of these firms
has exceeded 120 million square meters. Of the total housing,
residential apartments account for 84.5 percent, office buildings
comprise 4.49 percent, housing for commercial use account for 4.4
percent, factory buildings 3.1 percent, while housing for other
purposes 3.1 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
