<HEADLINE> Shandong Aims High in Hi-tech Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong province has
ambitiously formed ten hi-tech industrial groups with an annual
sales income expected to reach ten billion yuan by the end of the
century.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government plans to realize the goal by giving
top priority to the development of the ten hi-tech projects,
including leukocyte growth factor, high-performance magnetic
materials and related products, multi-functional optical fibre
information transmission system, computer-aided financial
management software and marine pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
This year, the provincial government has earmarked 20 million
yuan to fund the ten projects. In addition, it has
introduced a responsibility system - designating a chief expert to
supervise each of the ten project - to ensure success of the
work.  
