<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Greets Philippines' Independence Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today sent a message of greetings to his Philippine counterpart,
Fidel Ramos, on the 99th anniversary of the independence of the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
"On the occasion ... I wish to extend, on behalf of the Chinese
people and in my own name, our warm congratulations and best
wishes to Your Excellency, and through you, to the Government and
people of the Republic of the Philippines," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Since the establishment of diplomatic relations between China
and the Philippines 22 years ago, the friendly and cooperative
relations in all fields between our two countries have recorded
remarkable progress.
</P>
<P>
"The maintenance of the good-neighborly and friendly relations
between China and the Philippines conforms to the fundamental
interests of our two peoples and conduces to peace and stability
of this region.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that, under the concerted efforts of both
sides, Sino-Filipino relations will be consolidated and
strengthened steadily."
</P>
<P>
He wished prosperity of the republic and well-being of its
people.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines had been a Spanish colony since the 16th
century. General Emilio Aguinaldo declared independence of the
Philippines on June 12, 1898, with the help of the United States
which defeated Spain in the Spanish-American war.
</P>
<P>
It was placed under the American rule the same year and was
given internal self-government in 1935. The country was occupied
by Japan during the Second World War and American rule was
restored after the surrender of Japan in 1945. It became
independent on July 4, 1946. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
