<HEADLINE> Collins to Meet Oshana Challenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Ireland's Steve Collins will
defence his seventh WBO super-middleweight title when he faces
American Anwar Oshana at Glasgow's Kelvin Hall on July 5.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Oshana has an unbeaten record of 16 wins with
10 inside the distance, but is unlikely to pose the same threat as
previous challengers like Chris Eubank, Nigel Benn or Frenchman
Fredric Seillier.
</P>
<P>
Collins, who will be 33 a fortnight after the fight, won the
title by outpointing Eubank in Mill Street, County Cork, in March
1995.
</P>
<P>
He beat Eubank in his first defence then defeated Cornelius
Carr and Neville Brown in his following two fights. Then he twice
halted Benn before Seillier came along in the new year. 
</P>
