<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Population of Vicunas Increases in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The population of vicunas increased
from 66,600 to 94,000 throughout Peru in the past three years,
said a census report made by the Agriculture Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The report published today attributed the accomplishment to the
support of peasant communities responsible for the animal's
conservation, care and utilization.
</P>
<P>
The creation of the National Vicuna Society, which is currently
working in some 660 peasant communities in the high Andean areas
in Peru, has also led to the improvement and marketing of its wool
that is highly prized abroad, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The report said after the International Convention of the Sale
of Endangered Species declared it favored sustained and rational
protection of vicunas, measures were taken to support both
breeding and productive utilization of this species, threatened by
poachers and smugglers, following a policy of sustainable
development of natural resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
