<HEADLINE> Cold Wave Kills 14 People in Sao Paulo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people have died
from a cold snap which has hit southeastern Brazil over the
last 10 days, police said today.
</P>
<P>
Temperatures have fallen to as low as freezing, compared
with the seasonal norms of between 17 and 29 degrees centigrade,
the National Institute of Meteorology said.
</P>
<P>
In Sao Paolo, Brazil's largest city, the most recent victim of
the cold snap was identified as Jeronimo Alves, a 41-year-old
miner who died in the city's downtown area on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The cold killed a vagrant in Belo Horizonte in the
southeastern state of Minas Gerais on Tuesday where temperatures
dropped to zero and have caused three deaths since last week.
</P>
