<HEADLINE> Northeast Province to Host Fair on Forest Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, Jane 12 (Xinhua) -- A fair featuring forest products,
furniture, decorative materials and wood-working machinery is
expected to be held in northeast China's Heilongjiang province
from August 18 to 23, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 domestic companies and around 25 overseas
companies from France, Japan, Republic of Korea, Russia, Italy,
Great Britain, the Netherlands, Taiwan and Hong Kong will
reportedly to attend the fair, the second of its kind in the
province.
</P>
<P>
"During the fair, the companies will display logs, wood,
particle board, furniture, arts and crafts, decorative materials,
wood products, mountain products, wood-working machinery and
related products," the paper says, adding that some companies will
also seek co-operative projects during the fair.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang province is the largest wood producing province in
the country and has more than 200 varieties of wood, including
Korean pine, dragon spruce and birch, and nearly 10,000 forest
products manufacturing enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The fair will be organized jointly by the Heilongjiang
provincial government, the Ministry of Internal Trade, and the
China National Council of Light Industry.  
