<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan on Hong Kong (Part 3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When asked in what aspects Hong Kong will remain unchanged
after its return and what influence it will exert on the inland
areas, Li said: "Our government's resumption of exercising
sovereignty over Hong Kong marks our Chinese people's expunging a
century-old disgrace. It is of paramount importance in Chinese
people's hearts and becomes a focus of international
attention. Under Comrade Deng Xiaoping's great concept of "one
country, two systems", Hong Kong will keep its capitalist system
after its return.
</P>
<P>
"To be accurate, three things will remain as they are at
present: the social and economic system, the way of life and its
extant laws. We believe that the 'one country, two systems' policy
will be conducive to Hong Kong's sustained stability and
prosperity, our country's reforms and modernization, our country's
ultimate reunification with its other territories, our trade with
foreign nations and world peace.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong has contributed much to China's reforms and its
economic construction for more than a decade. For instance, about
half of foreign investments in China have come from or through
Hong Kong. More than half of China's exports have gone to Hong
Kong or gone to their destinations via the port city. Besides,
Hong Kong has served as a base of information, technology and
personnel for the inland areas. So we are quite confident that
with the economic development in inland areas, Hong Kong will play
a bigger role after its return.
</P>
<P>
"We're optimistic and confident about the future of Hong Kong
after its return. The compatriots in Hong Kong created the current
prosperity, it shows that they have enough wisdom and ability to
do well in governing Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Rapid economic growth, public stability, and the people's
solidarity in the interior areas provides powerful backing for the
long-term prosperity and stability of Hong Kong. Preparations for
resuming the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, and a smooth
transition, are progressing smoothly with concerted efforts from
different quarters.
</P>
<P>
"We believe our compatriots in Hong Kong, grasping their
destiny in their own hands, will surely perform new miracles in
the land of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Certainly we won't oversimplify the issues. The concept
of 'One country, two systems' is a new thing, we lack experiences
in many aspects. So two principles must be mentioned while talking
about the issue of Hong Kong, one is to be confident, the other is
to be circumspect."
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan also answered reporters' questions about Sino-Europe
relations, Sino-United States relations, and the issue of
Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
