<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Wheat Production to Fall in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Wheat output in Brazil will
fell 14 percent this year to 2.74 million tons, the National Basic
Commodities Company predicted today.
</P>
<P>
The drop has been blamed on a 16 percent reduction in the
planting area, which shrank from 1.75 million hectares in 1996 to
1.45 million this year, the organization said in its report.
</P>
<P>
It also foresaw a higher cereal imports of 5.54 million tons
this year to make up for the low yield. 
</P>
</TEXT>
