<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coffee Exports More Than Double </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Revenues generated from green
coffee bean exports in Brazil more than doubled in the first five
months of the year, the Brazilian Federation of Coffee Exporters
(Febec) said today in Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
In the five months, exports of green coffee beans reached 1.13
billion U.S. dollars, an increase of 253 percent compared with the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Febec said the average price of a 60-kilo sack of green coffee
beans hit 202.76 dollars in May due to the shortage of this
product in major coffee-importing countries.
</P>
<P>
In May, Brazilian coffee exports totaled 1.326 million sacks.
Between January and May, a total of 6.473 million sacks were
shipped abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
