<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader on Sino-German Ties, Human Rights (Part 1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, today outlined China's policies on Sino-German
relations, human rights and Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to developing its friendly and
cooperative ties with Germany, Li said in an interview with the
German newspaper "Die Welt", here today.
</P>
<P>
Generally speaking, China and Germany enjoyed good relations.
</P>
<P>
Li said Sino-German relations, which suffered twists and turns
in past years, have been brought back to a healthy and progressive
track after hard work by the two countries.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the two nations should sum up their
experience and draw lessons to avoid a repeat of such an
unpleasant performance.
</P>
<P>
"Germany is one of the most developed countries and China is
the largest developing nation in the world. The two countries
boast great complementarity in economies, and vast potential for
cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
Germany was China's largest economic and trade partner in
Europe, with its technical exports to China ranking first among
all European countries.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to continue comprehensive cooperation with Germany in
all respects including economy, trade, science and technology, and
culture and to make more achievements," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
