<HEADLINE> Film Fair Opened In Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong International Film
 Market, a trade fair which offers a wide range of local and
overseas films and TV programs, was opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Co-organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC)
and the Movie Producers and Distributors Association of Hong Kong,
 the three-day event attracted more than 70 local and overseas
exhibitors.
</P>
<P>
It is the first trade fair ever held in Hong Kong to highlight
the film industry.
</P>
<P>
TDC's Executive Director Michael Sze said at the opening
ceremony that the launch of the inaugural Film Market would
enhance Hong Kong's leading position as a production headquarters,
 international distribution base and exhibition capital for Asian
films and related products.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the world's third largest film producer after the
Untied States and India. It is also one of the largest film
exporters across the globe, with martial films in particular.
</P>
<P>
In tandem with the exhibition, a forum was staged for experts
from the Asia-Pacific region to present information on the latest
development of the film and television industry in their own
markets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
