<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Putonghua to Become Popular in Hong Kong Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A Putonghua festival is to be
launched in all primary and secondary schools in Hong Kong, in an
effort to encourage teachers and students to learn the most
commonly used spoken Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Starting from October 1, the three-month Putonghua Festival
will be mainly organized by the Hong Kong Putonghua Society, Hong
Kong Education Workers' Association and the Putonghua Channel of
Radio Television Hong Kong (RTHK).
</P>
<P>
Sin Kam Wai, chairman of the preparatory committee of the
festival, said that the event would be highlighted by a
listening-and-comprehension competition, which each school can
choose five students to take part in. The top five winners will
become Hong Kong's Putonghua messengers to travel to Shanghai,
the largest metropolis in China.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, schools are encouraged to hold various
activities helping students to learn Putonghua.
</P>
<P>
Sin, who is also principal of the 20-year-old Hong Kong
Putonghua Society, said: "We want all teachers and students to
realize that Putonghua is the common spoken language of the
Chinese nation. We hope that more and more Hongkongers can
communicate with other Chinese people in Putonghua."
</P>
<P>
Cantonese is a dialect widely used in Hong Kong, where
Putonghua is not as popular.
</P>
<P>
As the return of Hong Kong to her motherland is drawing near,
an increasing number of Hong Kong people are learning
Putonghua. Many schools have planned to teach Chinese in Putonghua
instead of Cantonese. Gift Talents School, a well-known primary
school in Hong Kong, has started from the third grade to teach
pupils Chinese in Putonghua, according to principal Leung Siu
Tong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
