<HEADLINE> HK Police Seize 8 Million HK Dollar Worth of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police seized five
kilograms of high-grade No.4 heroin following the arrest of a pair
 inside a squatter hut in Ngau Tam Mei Village, San Tin, Yuen Long
 today.
</P>
<P>
According to a police spokesman, officers from Kowloon East's
Regional Special Duty Squad have laid an ambush in the vicinity of
 the hut since 10 pm Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At about 6 am this morning, officers raided the hut and
arrested a 33-year-old man and a 36-year-old woman, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
A total of five kilograms of high-grade No.4 heroin, 13
kilograms of additives as well as some manufacturing equipment
were found inside the premises.
</P>
<P>
The seized drugs, which could fetch a market value of about 8.1
million HK dollars (1.05 million US dollars) after dilution, is
believed to be supplied to the drug market in East Kowloon, the
spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
