<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mandela Meets Libyan Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela met visiting Libyan Foreign Minister Omar
Muntasser yesterday, but had not offered his country as a neutral
territory for the Lockerbie air disaster trial.
</P>
<P>
A foreign ministry spokesman said today that the issue had not
been raised by either man although it had been discussed by
foreign minister Alfred Nzo and Muntasser.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Muntasser had private discussion with
Mandela and details would not be made public.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations imposed sanctions against Libya in 1992
because of Libya's insistance on a neutral venue for the trial of
two of its citizens suspected to have been involved in the 1988
Lockerbie air disaster.
</P>
<P>
More than 250 people died when a Pan American aircraft
exploded over the town of Lockerbie in Scottland.
</P>
<P>
The matter of a neutral venue had been discussed in talks
between Nzo and Muntasser,the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Nzo had expressed South Africa's support, in line with
resolution of the Organisation of African Unity (OAU), that the
suspects should be tried by Scottish judges under Scottish law in
a neutral territory.
</P>
<P>
But according to the spokesman, South Africa had not been
offered as a venue.
</P>
<P>
In January, after talks with Muntasser ahead of OAU council of
foreign minister's meeting in the Libyan capital,Tripoli, Nzo
said his government would consider offering South Africa as a
neutral venue if requested to do so.
</P>
<P>
Muntasser, after meeting Nzo on Monday, repeated the two
suspects were willing to subject themselves to a trial in a
neutral country.
</P>
<P>
The Libyan foreign minister is in South Africa for an official
visit.
</P>
<P>
Britain, France and the United States are demanding the
extradition of the suspects to Scottland to stand trial.They have
rejected Libya's offer to deliver the two men to the
international court or to a neutral country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
