<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Party's Absolute Leadership Over the Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today stressed that the Chinese Communist Party has absolute
authority over the army, and that the army can be modernized as
long as the correct development path is followed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also General Secretary of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) Central Committee and Chairman of the Central Military
Commission (CMC), made the remark when meeting here with some
deputies to the CPC Congress of the Air Force.
</P>
<P>
He congratulated yesterday's convening of the congress, and
greeted the deputies and the rank and file of the Air Force on
behalf of the CPC Central Committee and the CMC.
</P>
<P>
Since the Air Force was founded 48 years ago, it has made
important contributions to national defense and preparations
against war, and carried out rescue work and disaster relief, the
president noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized that the CPC Central Committee and the CMC
attach great importance to the Air Force, which plays a
significant role in safeguarding state sovereignty and security.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the hope that the Air Force will follow the command
of the CPC Central Committee and the CMC, so as to maintain the
Party's absolute leadership over the army and improve its overall
quality and its combat effectiveness in the hi-tech age. Doing so
will help build it into a strong and modernized force.
</P>
<P>
The congress required the rank and file to rally more closely
around the CPC Central Committee and the CMC with Jiang Zemin at
the core, and firmly follow their command and direction, and to
greet the convocation of the 15th CPC National Congress scheduled
for this autumn.  
</P>
</TEXT>
