<HEADLINE> Kinkel: Poland Top Candidate for EU, NATO Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel
said today that Poland was among the top candidates for joining
the European Union (EU) and the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO).
</P>
<P>
Kinkel made the remarks while meeting with visiting Polish
Foreign Minister Dariusz Rosati.
</P>
<P>
They both agreed that the enlargement of EU or NATO should
contribute to the stability in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel praised Poland's tremendous efforts to qualify for
membership of the two organizations, and noted that any member
country of NATO enjoys full right and bears equal responsibility
as others.
</P>
<P>
In the process of its eastward expansion, NATO should help
boost the military integration of the new members with it and
provide political cooperation, Kinkel said, adding that meanwhile,
the new member states could in advance join the works of some
committees under the western alliance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
