<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola to Implement Education Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government will soon
implement an elementary and vocational education plan for youth
out of school.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the plan is to increase job opportunities for
the large number of youth, especially those in the countryside
through fundamental education and vocational education in such
fields as agriculture, sewing, carpentry, taloring, fishery,
sundry goods sales, construction, machinery industry, welding and
piping erection.
</P>
<P>
It will take five years to carry out the plan beginning this
July. The first two years are the experimental stage during which
two training centers will be set up in Luanda province and Huambo
province in the central part of the country to provide
three-month and six-month curriculums for 920 youth. Some war
damaged educational facilities will be repaired during this
period.
</P>
<P>
The second stage which will take three years will consolidate
and enhance the experience gained during the first stage and
extend the plan to four or six more provinces and then to the
country as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The plan will be targeted at 14 to 30 year old youth,
especially females, peasants and demobilized armymen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
