<HEADLINE> 10,000 Homing Pigeons Fly from HK to Mark Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A total of 10,000 homing pigeons
from various provinces of China's mainland will be released from
Hong Kong on July 1 this year, just hours after Hong Kong's
handover at mid-night on June 30, and the pigeons will then fly
all the way back to their hometowns.
</P>
<P>
The pigeons will be brought here on June 29 to get ready for
the special ceremony to mark the handover, it was announced here
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The event is jointly organized by Hong Kong's Regional Council,
the Chinese State Physical Culture and Sports Commission, and the
Chinese Racing Pigeon Association.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here today, Adolf Hsu, Director
of the Regional Services Department, said that the pigeons' return
to their homeland symbolized Hong Kong's return to her motherland.
</P>
<P>
The pigeon-releasing ceremony at the Sha Tin Sports Ground will
be accompanied with performances by popular singers, children's
choir and Chinese dance.
</P>
<P>
The estimated budget for the event is 700,000 HK dollars
(89,700 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The pigeons, picked up and trained in 31 Chinese provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions, are scheduled to assemble
at Shenzhen, right to the north of Hong Kong, sometime after June
20, it was announced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
