<HEADLINE> Former Japanese PM Confident of Hong Kong's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Former Japanese Prime Minister
Tsutomu Hata says he is confident that Hong Kong will enjoy more
stability and prosperity under the "one country, two systems"
principle after China resumes exercising sovereignty over Hong
Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua News Agency on Tuesday,
he said Hong Kong's return to its motherland is the greatest event
of the age.
</P>
<P>
As the president of the Japanese Dietmen's League for
Japan-Hong Kong and the leader of the Sun Party, Hata still lives
an active political life and has been much concerned about Hong
Kong's future.
</P>
<P>
Hata said he admired the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's
insight, wisdom and his concept of "one country, two systems",
which has played a key role in the peaceful solution of the Hong
Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on Hong Kong's future, he said it will continue to
serve as Asia's financial and trade center, maintain its
prosperity and achieve steady development. This is a situation
from which China, Asia and even the world will benefit, he said.
</P>
<P>
The successful solution of the Hong Kong issue under the
principle of "one country, two systems" will exert positive
effects on China's ultimate reunification with its other
territories, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hata also noted that there is only one China and that the
Taiwan issue is China's internal affair. Hong Kong's sustained
prosperity and magnetism to foreign investors, businessmen and
common people desirous of living there will be helpful to the
ultimate solution of the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
He finally said that as China's true friend, he would be
present at the ceremony for Hong Kong's return to witness the
arrival of the great historic moment and to experience its
significance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
