<HEADLINE> Market Capitalization at Karachi Stock Exchange Rises: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's capital market
recorded a bullish trend with an increase in the aggregate market
capitalization at the Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE) despite
experiencing decline in the first six months of the current fiscal
year, an economic survey said today.
</P>
<P>
Depicting the trends of the stock market, the Economic Survey
for 1996-97 said that total turnover of shares at KSE increased by
62 percent from 3524 million shares during July-March 1995-96 to
5707 million shares during the first nine months of the current
year.
</P>
<P>
Aggregate market capitalization at KSE increased by 32.7
percent from 365.24 billion rupees (about 9 billion U.S. dollars)
on June 30, 1996 to 484.55 billion rupees (about 12 billion U.S.
dollars) on March 31, 1997, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
However, the State Bank of Pakistan general index of share
prices declined by five percent during July-March 1996-97, it
said.  
</P>
