<HEADLINE> 11,327 Tons of Clove Harvested in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Clove growers have earned
three billion Tanzania Shillings (about 5 million U.S. Dollars)
from the sale of 11,327 tons of the spice harvested between July
1996 and March 1997.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Trade, Industries and Marketing Khamis Ahmada
said Tuesday that the just ended crop season was almost 10 times
higher than the 1995/96 season.
</P>
<P>
The government managed to mobilize the people to participate
in picking the spice despite "the clandestine campaign" waged by
the opposition, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
He did not say how many tons of clove have been exported
during the period.
</P>
<P>
Besiders Zanzibar, cloves are grown in Indonesia, Brazil and
other Indian Ocean islands of Comoros, Mauritius, and Madagascar.
</P>
