<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets ended mixed today after an unsteady start on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
On London market, British FTSE-100 index ended lower after
briefly opening at a record level. It ran out of steam following a
hefty four percent rise the previous four sessions. Britain's
equities had looked to Wall Street for fresh incentive to push
higher but an unsteady start in New York dragged the FTSE back to
the worst level of the day. The FTSE-100 finished 14.8 points off
at 4,724.8.
</P>
