Frankfurt market drew some strength from overnight gains on Wall
Street and placed uncertainty about monetary union on the
backburner. The DAX index advanced 12.42 points to close the floor
session at 3,677.43 points.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, French shares closed higher but off the day's highs
after a late interruption in trade caused by a storm. The CAC-40
index finished up 32.01 points at 2,696.19. 
