<HEADLINE> Arab Strategy for Combat of Terrorism Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The General Secretariat of the
Council of Arab Ministers of the Interior announced today a
project plan for the implementation on stages of an Arab strategy
for combatting terrorism.
</P>
<P>
A statement released by the Secretariat said that the project
defines the mechanism and method of implementation of the plan,
as well as its execution program and means of financing.
</P>
<P>
The three-year project plan calls for the convocation of a
meeting of officials in charge of combatting terrorism in the
Arab states to examine common issues, coordination of
anti-terrorism plans and establishment of a data center which
will accumulate data on all forms of terrorism at the local,
regional and international levels.
</P>
<P>
The project plan also calls for the preparation of a model
Arab law for the combat of terrorism, the drafting of an Arab
information plan to educate Arab citizens about the dangers of
terrorism, and enhancing Arab presence in international
organizations concerned with the combat of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the project plan will be submitted to
the 15th session of the Council of Arab Interior Ministers due to
take place early next year for ratification and subsequent
implementation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
