<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SADC to Implement Sub-Regional Energy Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Southern African
Development Community (SADC) is planning to implement in the
sub-region 52 energy projects worth 928 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Acting Energy Commissioner in the Tanzanian Ministry of Energy
and Minerals Bashiri Mrindoko, who is attending the on-going 22nd
SADC energy meeting in Tanzania's northern town of Arusha, said
630 million U.S. Dollars are already in place and the balance is
yet to be secured.
</P>
<P>
The projects cover the areas of electricity, petroleum and
energy conservation, according to an official attending the
meeting which started on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian government is funding the SADC regional energy
project while the Canadian Development Agency is financing the
industrial energy management scheme aimed at improving efficiency
in energy consumption to avoid wastage of energy resources.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch government is financing the small-scale energy
enterprises program including market assessments and business
planning.
</P>
<P>
High on the agenda of the meeting include finalizing of the
SADC energy cooperation policy, preparation for the launching of
the SADC joint petroleum exploration, and protection rural energy
environment.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is being attended by officials from Zambia, South
Africa, Angola, Mauritius, Zimbabwe, Botswana, Swaziland,
Namibia, Malawi and Tanzania. Another similar meeting was held
last year in Swaziland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
