<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-11 19:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish PM Reiterates to Respect China's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin
Erbakan has reiterated Turkey's stance to respect China's
sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with a delegation from the Chinese National
People's Congress (NPC) headed by Zhou Jue, vice chairman of the
NPC Foreign Affairs Committee here Tuesday evening, Erbakan said
that Turkey does not allow any organization or people in Turkey
to take any political activities against China.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, he said that the Turkish government
would stick to its "one China" policy, recognizing the People's
Republic of China as the sole legitimate government of China.
</P>
<P>
Erbakan stressed that Turkey and China have no reasons
not to enhance cooperation as the cooperation is a trend toward
the development of the bilateral ties between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and China are the two important states in Asia and
Turkey attaches great importance to the relations between the
two countries, said Erbakan, adding that Ankara and Beijing
should make joint efforts to promote their economic and trade
ties.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Turkish businessmen would invest
in China and Chinese businessmen would come to Turkey for the
same purpose.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese NPC delegation arrived in Turkey on June 5 for a
one-week good-will visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
