<DOCNO> XIE19970612.0324 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Financing for Education Modernization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today approved a 58.1 million U.S. dollar loan to
Panama to help improve the quality, efficiency and accessibility
of education from preschool to 12th grade.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be utilized to support the Ministry of
Education in the modernization of curriculum, teachers training,
development and acquisition of learning materials, as well as
improvement of evaluation and management systems.
</P>
<P>
In line with the six-year program, students scores on
attainment tests are expected to rise by 20 percent and the
percentage of students completing sixth grade is expected to rise
from 78 percent in 1997 to some 90 percent in 2002. Enrollment in
preschool and higher secondary grades is also expected to rise
substantially.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is estimated at 73.3 million
dollars. In addition to the IDB loan, local counterpart funds
total 15.2 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the World Bank has agreed to provide a 38 million
dollar loan to Panama to back a complementary educational
modernization project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
